1
00:00:35,969 --> 00:00:36,969
(All characters, organizations, and events...)

2
00:00:36,969 --> 00:00:38,009
(in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:38,009 --> 00:00:39,008
(Child actors were accompanied by family and were kept safe.)

4
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:44,888
Why didn't you come to report to me?

5
00:00:48,288 --> 00:00:49,957
Didn't you hear from the president?

6
00:00:50,457 --> 00:00:52,328
- The embezzlement... - Forget it.

7
00:00:52,428 --> 00:00:53,867
This is my decision.

8
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:56,727
Ms. Yu is transferred as planned to the Florida office.

9
00:00:56,867 --> 00:00:57,898
End of story.

10
00:00:58,137 --> 00:00:59,738
The company can't take a hit.

11
00:00:59,838 --> 00:01:02,508
It's wrong to ignore an embezzlement case.

12
00:01:03,268 --> 00:01:05,137
- Please change your mind. - I don't want to.

13
00:01:05,137 --> 00:01:08,207
I joined because I was promised full authority to investigate.

14
00:01:09,777 --> 00:01:10,978
Please consider...

15
00:01:11,217 --> 00:01:12,448
my decision.

16
00:01:14,247 --> 00:01:15,418
It's annoying, isn't it?

17
00:01:15,418 --> 00:01:16,688
But what can you do?

18
00:01:17,258 --> 00:01:20,217
The authority you hid behind to carry out your duty...

19
00:01:20,758 --> 00:01:21,957
now depends on me.

20
00:01:23,857 --> 00:01:25,827
(Audit Team Gu Han Soo, Unmute)

21
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:28,567
- Mr. Gu. - Yes.

22
00:01:28,698 --> 00:01:29,768
Stop Ms. Yu...

23
00:01:30,838 --> 00:01:32,137
from going to the airport.

24
00:01:32,768 --> 00:01:34,868
Do whatever it takes to stop her.

25
00:01:34,868 --> 00:01:36,008
Yes, sir.

26
00:01:39,237 --> 00:01:40,308
Shin Cha Il.

27
00:01:41,047 --> 00:01:42,178
You're fired.

28
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:03,937
What is this punk doing?

29
00:02:05,237 --> 00:02:07,338
Move! Get out of my way!

30
00:02:07,668 --> 00:02:08,808
Move.

31
00:02:10,508 --> 00:02:11,637
What's wrong with him?

32
00:02:14,877 --> 00:02:16,178
All of them are crazy.

33
00:02:16,747 --> 00:02:18,448
What's wrong with you? Move.

34
00:02:19,277 --> 00:02:21,148
Ms. Yu is not allowed to go to the airport.

35
00:02:21,887 --> 00:02:23,547
We haven't finished auditing her.

36
00:02:35,728 --> 00:02:40,767
(The Auditors)

37
00:02:41,237 --> 00:02:43,107
(Episode 4)

38
00:02:49,978 --> 00:02:52,017
(Director Yang Jae Seung)

39
00:02:53,448 --> 00:02:55,348
- How did it go? - Well...

40
00:02:55,348 --> 00:02:57,557
Ms. Yu got in Mr. Shin's car...

41
00:02:57,758 --> 00:03:00,357
and voluntarily left for the police station.

42
00:03:00,387 --> 00:03:03,758
I'm told you'd understand if I say this.

43
00:03:09,528 --> 00:03:11,867
(Vice President Hwang Dae Woong)

44
00:03:22,348 --> 00:03:23,778
I fired Shin Cha Il.

45
00:03:24,077 --> 00:03:26,318
He ignored an order from his direct superior.

46
00:03:26,978 --> 00:03:28,647
Write up the dismissal notice.

47
00:03:29,748 --> 00:03:31,788
I'm going to throw it in his face.

48
00:03:32,318 --> 00:03:34,057
I gave you the authority over the Auditing Team,

49
00:03:34,057 --> 00:03:36,087
not over firing Mr. Shin.

50
00:03:37,598 --> 00:03:38,897
Are you joking with me?

51
00:03:39,897 --> 00:03:42,068
Didn't I warn you the construction will be stopped?

52
00:03:43,028 --> 00:03:44,137
Do you want to step down?

53
00:03:44,468 --> 00:03:46,538
But the construction won't stop, will it?

54
00:03:47,568 --> 00:03:49,307
You wouldn't let your hard-earned...

55
00:03:49,307 --> 00:03:50,878
Inpo Apartment construction stop.

56
00:03:51,778 --> 00:03:53,337
After all, you hate suffering a loss.

57
00:03:54,878 --> 00:03:57,278
You have the authority over Ms. Yu's audit.

58
00:03:57,378 --> 00:03:58,378
Use it well.

59
00:03:58,378 --> 00:03:59,778
What will I do with...

60
00:03:59,778 --> 00:04:01,288
the Audit Team Manager who doesn't listen to me?

61
00:04:02,887 --> 00:04:04,017
What are you after?

62
00:04:15,228 --> 00:04:16,427
I have a prior engagement.

63
00:04:22,168 --> 00:04:24,107
(President Hwang Se Woong)

64
00:04:42,087 --> 00:04:44,028
- Hey. - What happened?

65
00:04:44,128 --> 00:04:46,927
Mr. Shin took Ms. Yu to the police station.

66
00:04:47,057 --> 00:04:48,668
Didn't the Vice President Hwang order him to let her be?

67
00:04:48,668 --> 00:04:50,067
That's impossible.

68
00:04:50,197 --> 00:04:51,538
She should be arrested for pocketing money.

69
00:04:51,538 --> 00:04:53,098
Forget about that.

70
00:04:53,098 --> 00:04:54,968
A worker should follow the company's order.

71
00:04:54,968 --> 00:04:56,838
Mr. Shin made the wrong call this time.

72
00:04:57,038 --> 00:04:58,307
He didn't.

73
00:04:58,677 --> 00:04:59,838
We'll get the money back.

74
00:04:59,838 --> 00:05:01,648
The longest sentence you'll get

75
00:05:01,648 --> 00:05:03,408
for 3.4 million dollars is 3 to 4 years.

76
00:05:03,447 --> 00:05:04,877
It's like getting a million-dollar annual salary...

77
00:05:04,877 --> 00:05:05,877
in jail.

78
00:05:05,947 --> 00:05:07,218
So would you return the money?

79
00:05:07,218 --> 00:05:08,518
We'll find the money.

80
00:05:09,288 --> 00:05:11,088
We will, period.

81
00:05:11,088 --> 00:05:13,687
Go ahead. Go and find that money.

82
00:05:14,127 --> 00:05:15,187
Find it, all right?

83
00:05:15,388 --> 00:05:17,057
Stop spouting nonsense.

84
00:05:18,158 --> 00:05:19,197
Great work.

85
00:05:23,668 --> 00:05:25,398
So, what do you think of your new manager?

86
00:05:25,638 --> 00:05:26,838
Is he stressing you out?

87
00:05:26,838 --> 00:05:28,168
The so-called president of the company...

88
00:05:28,168 --> 00:05:30,737
hired externally just to kick me out.

89
00:05:30,978 --> 00:05:34,478
This darned company. I had no one to count on,

90
00:05:34,778 --> 00:05:36,877
so I'm happy to know that you've got my back, kiddo.

91
00:05:36,877 --> 00:05:38,848
That money is the death benefit from the car accident.

92
00:05:38,848 --> 00:05:41,687
How will my grandkids survive after I die?

93
00:05:53,028 --> 00:05:54,067
I'm...

94
00:05:54,497 --> 00:05:57,067
only going with you to stop this absurdity.

95
00:05:57,997 --> 00:05:59,697
I can catch tomorrow's flight.

96
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:05,078
The investigation will resume based on the union rep's testimony.

97
00:06:05,278 --> 00:06:08,208
You'll be banned from leaving the country, Ms. Yu.

98
00:06:08,278 --> 00:06:10,148
The company will take my side.

99
00:06:10,617 --> 00:06:12,218
And you'll get fired.

100
00:06:12,218 --> 00:06:13,377
I don't care.

101
00:06:13,947 --> 00:06:15,547
Why are you doing this to me?

102
00:06:15,747 --> 00:06:16,848
You embezzled money.

103
00:06:18,718 --> 00:06:21,458
Kang Myung Chul must've promised to go to the US once things died down.

104
00:06:21,728 --> 00:06:23,898
He would've hidden the money until then.

105
00:06:24,458 --> 00:06:27,098
What kind of a life did you dream of with 3.4 million dollars?

106
00:06:27,468 --> 00:06:28,968
Living in a house with a pool...

107
00:06:28,968 --> 00:06:31,297
and a large garden, raising a dog,

108
00:06:31,437 --> 00:06:33,538
wearing designer clothes, and eating high-quality food.

109
00:06:34,437 --> 00:06:37,208
However, you'll live in a room with bars, be watched by dogs,

110
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:39,838
wear a prison uniform, and eat distributed food.

111
00:06:40,807 --> 00:06:41,848
I...

112
00:06:43,677 --> 00:06:44,817
will have you...

113
00:06:45,677 --> 00:06:46,747
receive discipline.

114
00:07:01,468 --> 00:07:04,697
(Dosam Police Station)

115
00:07:12,838 --> 00:07:14,648
(Dosam Police Station)

116
00:07:21,747 --> 00:07:24,057
(Dosam Police Station)

117
00:07:31,797 --> 00:07:33,658
An office worker must take care of their stomach.

118
00:07:33,658 --> 00:07:35,367
Mr. Shin will probably be back late.

119
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:37,197
We should eat for our brains to work.

120
00:07:38,197 --> 00:07:39,197
Why don't we eat?

121
00:07:39,997 --> 00:07:41,408
Let's refuel with some food.

122
00:07:41,468 --> 00:07:43,237
Today's lunch is bulgogi hot pot.

123
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,408
Gosh. It's not even Korean beef,

124
00:07:45,408 --> 00:07:48,007
yet bulgogi hot pot is crazy expensive.

125
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,388
Aren't you going for lunch?

126
00:07:55,447 --> 00:07:56,487
I'm not hungry.

127
00:08:01,728 --> 00:08:04,997
If we cross-exam the two, we'll find the money.

128
00:08:06,797 --> 00:08:08,328
I simply have no appetite.

129
00:08:09,627 --> 00:08:10,697
Got it.

130
00:08:21,648 --> 00:08:22,708
- My gosh. - Goodness.

131
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:26,148
An audit notice is all it takes to make the food taste better.

132
00:08:27,148 --> 00:08:29,447
It's the end for Mr. Shin.

133
00:08:29,817 --> 00:08:31,458
I've never seen anyone survive...

134
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:33,158
after going against the Vice President Hwang.

135
00:08:34,057 --> 00:08:35,658
Do you hate Mr. Shin that much?

136
00:08:35,658 --> 00:08:38,228
Of course. He's screwing up our Audit Team.

137
00:08:38,297 --> 00:08:39,958
Are you happy with that? Are you?

138
00:08:40,158 --> 00:08:42,297
I would so love to transfer to a different department.

139
00:08:42,427 --> 00:08:44,937
But look around. Come on.

140
00:08:45,138 --> 00:08:47,607
Nobody wants to eat around us.

141
00:08:48,038 --> 00:08:49,538
We've made too many enemies,

142
00:08:49,538 --> 00:08:51,538
auditing every single department. I've got nowhere to go.

143
00:08:51,807 --> 00:08:54,278
But the Audit Team corrects wrongdoings,

144
00:08:54,278 --> 00:08:55,348
so why did we make enemies?

145
00:08:56,677 --> 00:08:57,747
You're frustrating.

146
00:08:58,918 --> 00:09:01,848
This is why a worker like you is called a rookie.

147
00:09:01,848 --> 00:09:04,658
Got it, you clueless Gu Han Soo?

148
00:09:04,658 --> 00:09:07,087
It's wrong for people to make us their enemy...

149
00:09:07,317 --> 00:09:09,758
simply because we audit them.

150
00:09:10,528 --> 00:09:12,797
That's what I think. Excuse me. Enjoy your lunch.

151
00:09:13,227 --> 00:09:15,927
You're my main enemy. Understood? My main enemy.

152
00:09:16,398 --> 00:09:18,168
He talks back a lot now.

153
00:09:18,837 --> 00:09:20,498
What's more is that... Oh, by the way,

154
00:09:20,668 --> 00:09:22,508
you have your hair down, sir.

155
00:09:22,508 --> 00:09:24,177
It suits you.

156
00:09:24,177 --> 00:09:25,638
I have too little hair for that.

157
00:09:25,638 --> 00:09:29,477
The order of rank in the company is totally messed... No.

158
00:09:30,148 --> 00:09:33,577
The order of rank is a total disaster.

159
00:09:33,817 --> 00:09:34,947
A low-level employee is...

160
00:09:34,947 --> 00:09:37,347
getting in my way, even though I'm a director.

161
00:09:37,347 --> 00:09:39,918
And Mr. Shin is trying to get me fired.

162
00:09:39,918 --> 00:09:42,628
- He glares at me... - Shut it, will you?

163
00:09:50,797 --> 00:09:51,837
Yes?

164
00:09:58,638 --> 00:10:01,947
The union rep testified that it was a lone crime.

165
00:10:02,807 --> 00:10:05,177
I feel bad that your disciplinary measures fell through.

166
00:10:05,847 --> 00:10:08,087
We won't see each other again, so let me tell you this.

167
00:10:08,618 --> 00:10:10,618
Back then and even now,

168
00:10:11,187 --> 00:10:12,587
you're too idealistic.

169
00:10:16,957 --> 00:10:18,998
(Dosam Police Station)

170
00:10:23,927 --> 00:10:25,437
(Dosam Police Station)

171
00:10:32,437 --> 00:10:33,977
(Vice President Hwang Dae Woong)

172
00:10:36,047 --> 00:10:37,148
This is Shin Cha Il.

173
00:10:37,378 --> 00:10:39,677
Stop running wild. You're already fired.

174
00:10:39,817 --> 00:10:42,118
There must be a formal dismissal procedure in writing.

175
00:10:43,788 --> 00:10:44,918
What will you do now?

176
00:10:44,918 --> 00:10:46,288
The embezzlement was orchestrated by an employee,

177
00:10:46,288 --> 00:10:48,258
but you made it look like the union rep did it alone,

178
00:10:48,258 --> 00:10:49,788
so we'll have to audit you, Mr. Hwang.

179
00:10:50,227 --> 00:10:51,258
You're saying I did it?

180
00:10:51,258 --> 00:10:53,297
Didn't you send an attorney to the union rep and make a deal?

181
00:10:53,297 --> 00:10:55,028
A reduction in sentence and some money.

182
00:10:55,028 --> 00:10:56,498
You're amazing.

183
00:10:56,498 --> 00:10:58,567
What a waste that we don't get along.

184
00:11:01,008 --> 00:11:02,908
Cancel Ms. Yu's transfer.

185
00:11:03,008 --> 00:11:05,038
Keep the union rep's statement as it was.

186
00:11:05,738 --> 00:11:07,977
Then your mistake can be undone.

187
00:11:07,977 --> 00:11:10,408
- There won't be any audit, either. - Your threat is laughable.

188
00:11:10,408 --> 00:11:12,717
The company must take responsibility for its workers.

189
00:11:12,878 --> 00:11:15,118
That's easy for you to say since it's not your money.

190
00:11:16,187 --> 00:11:18,388
I only do what will benefit me.

191
00:11:18,988 --> 00:11:21,258
Finding the money and returning it to the union members...

192
00:11:21,258 --> 00:11:22,988
will bring many benefits to you.

193
00:11:23,327 --> 00:11:26,197
The company's reputation and the workers' devotion will rise.

194
00:11:26,197 --> 00:11:27,227
And if the money is lost forever?

195
00:11:28,297 --> 00:11:29,427
Will you take responsibility?

196
00:11:39,408 --> 00:11:40,577
I will.

197
00:11:41,378 --> 00:11:42,408
I will hand in...

198
00:11:43,278 --> 00:11:44,378
my resignation letter.

199
00:11:46,317 --> 00:11:48,648
Is your resignation letter worth 3.4 million dollars?

200
00:11:52,518 --> 00:11:55,288
The conditions must fit the bill to make a deal, you punk.

201
00:11:55,687 --> 00:11:57,288
I'll take your resignation letter...

202
00:11:57,358 --> 00:11:59,057
as collateral for the 3.4 million dollars.

203
00:11:59,697 --> 00:12:00,758
Get us back the money,

204
00:12:00,758 --> 00:12:01,998
or you'll have to cough it up somehow.

205
00:12:01,998 --> 00:12:02,998
How about it?

206
00:12:04,168 --> 00:12:05,238
Fine.

207
00:12:06,498 --> 00:12:08,608
Yu Mi Kyung's transfer has just been canceled.

208
00:12:08,837 --> 00:12:10,837
You take care of the union rep's testimony.

209
00:12:11,038 --> 00:12:12,108
Three days is all you have.

210
00:12:12,608 --> 00:12:14,477
If you fail to settle it by then,

211
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:17,108
Ms. Yu will be sent to the US right away,

212
00:12:17,207 --> 00:12:19,977
and you'll be blamed for the 3.4 million dollars.

213
00:12:37,738 --> 00:12:39,437
(Audit Team Manager Shin Cha Il)

214
00:12:40,238 --> 00:12:41,707
Yes, this is Gu Han Soo.

215
00:12:42,608 --> 00:12:45,408
The union rep testified that it was a lone act.

216
00:12:46,538 --> 00:12:48,807
Ms. Yu won't fly out for the next three days.

217
00:12:49,278 --> 00:12:51,918
I'll look into what Kang Myung Chul is thinking.

218
00:12:51,918 --> 00:12:54,587
You are to pass on the situation to the others.

219
00:12:54,888 --> 00:12:55,918
Understood.

220
00:13:12,337 --> 00:13:14,837
We need the energy to work now.

221
00:13:15,508 --> 00:13:17,608
The union rep stated it was a lone crime.

222
00:13:18,337 --> 00:13:20,778
We're the ones who have to find the money now.

223
00:13:21,778 --> 00:13:24,047
Was Vice President Hwang behind it?

224
00:13:25,378 --> 00:13:26,418
Yes.

225
00:13:28,547 --> 00:13:29,587
Make sure to have some.

226
00:13:45,138 --> 00:13:48,337
The Audit Team exists to ensure ethical management.

227
00:13:49,937 --> 00:13:51,138
Ethical management is...

228
00:13:51,408 --> 00:13:53,608
the most important company value these days.

229
00:14:02,618 --> 00:14:05,087
Any intellectual is expected to obey...

230
00:14:05,087 --> 00:14:07,957
the code of conduct I've explained so far.

231
00:14:08,227 --> 00:14:09,288
Ladies and gentlemen,

232
00:14:09,358 --> 00:14:11,158
I hope you can all work with passion.

233
00:14:11,998 --> 00:14:13,797
That's it for the lecture. Thank you.

234
00:14:14,827 --> 00:14:16,768
(The Myeong Code of Conduct)

235
00:14:19,498 --> 00:14:21,707
(The Myeong Code of Conduct)

236
00:14:28,108 --> 00:14:30,108
The man who sexually harassed my wife is...

237
00:14:30,108 --> 00:14:31,148
visiting me at work?

238
00:14:31,677 --> 00:14:32,817
I should report you to the police.

239
00:14:32,817 --> 00:14:34,788
Ms. Yu Mi Kyung's transfer has been canceled.

240
00:14:38,087 --> 00:14:39,158
It's only a matter of time...

241
00:14:39,158 --> 00:14:41,087
before we confirm that you were in it with her.

242
00:14:41,827 --> 00:14:43,258
And now, you're threatening me?

243
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:45,957
This is serious.

244
00:14:45,957 --> 00:14:47,597
If you quit now, you'll look suspicious.

245
00:14:47,597 --> 00:14:49,498
If you spend the money, we'll track your funds.

246
00:14:49,998 --> 00:14:51,437
You're in a difficult situation now.

247
00:14:52,998 --> 00:14:54,038
Well...

248
00:14:54,908 --> 00:14:58,337
Why are you worried about me?

249
00:14:59,138 --> 00:15:01,248
Snap out of it, Mr. Shin Cha Il.

250
00:15:02,807 --> 00:15:04,278
The Audit Team's manager...

251
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,518
who holds lectures on professional ethics...

252
00:15:07,347 --> 00:15:08,748
committed embezzlement?

253
00:15:09,047 --> 00:15:10,087
"Embezzlement?"

254
00:15:14,957 --> 00:15:16,258
There's some dust here.

255
00:15:39,418 --> 00:15:41,288
Stop putting on an act.

256
00:15:41,418 --> 00:15:43,187
Why the long face? Don't fake it in front of me.

257
00:15:43,947 --> 00:15:45,317
I know you're all excited inside.

258
00:15:47,258 --> 00:15:48,258
Sit.

259
00:15:51,898 --> 00:15:53,398
Your transfer has been canceled.

260
00:15:54,868 --> 00:15:57,297
- Pardon me? - I gave Shin Cha Il three days,

261
00:15:58,197 --> 00:16:00,168
so just lie low for the next three days.

262
00:16:01,937 --> 00:16:03,008
Where's the money?

263
00:16:07,077 --> 00:16:08,847
Hide it well in a safe place...

264
00:16:08,977 --> 00:16:10,047
and guard it with your life.

265
00:16:12,118 --> 00:16:13,118
You can go.

266
00:16:33,998 --> 00:16:36,108
I was told the 50-dollar bills were all checked, bundled, and sealed...

267
00:16:36,368 --> 00:16:38,608
and that they could all be traced with the serial numbers.

268
00:16:38,878 --> 00:16:40,207
I'm not an idiot.

269
00:16:40,577 --> 00:16:41,947
Knowing that,

270
00:16:42,278 --> 00:16:44,847
